context: In Rajasthan, <a0_0><b5_0>Jodhpur and Kota<b5_0/><a0_0/> are two major educational hubs. Kota is known for its quality education in preparation of various competitive exams, coaching for medical and engineering exams while <a1_0>Jodhpur<a1_0/> is home to many higher educational institutions like IIT, AIIMS, National Law University, Sardar Patel Police University, National institute of Fashion Technology, MBM Engineering College etc. Kota is popularly referred to as, <b6_0>"<a2_0>coaching capital of India<a2_0/>"<b6_0/>. Other major educational institutions are Birla Institute of Technology and Science Pilani, Malaviya National Institute of Technology Jaipur, IIM Udaipur r and LNMIIT. Rajasthan has <a3_0>nine<a3_0/> universities and <b7_0>more than 250<b7_0/> colleges, 55,000 primary and 7,400 secondary schools. There are <a4_0>41 engineering colleges<a4_0/> with an annual enrollment of <b8_0>about 11,500 students<b8_0/>. Apart from above there 41 Private universities like Amity University Rajasthan, Jaipur,Manipal University Jaipur, OPJS University, Churu, Mody University of Technology and Science Lakshmangarh (Women's University, Sikar), RNB Global University, Bikaner. The state has <b9_0>23<b9_0/> polytechnic colleges and 152 Industrial Training Institutes (ITIs) that impart vocational training.
